
=Status Report 2010=

Dion Hinchcliffe:

"Drupal has apparently won the social CMS wars in the open source space with literally tens of millions of users. With this, traditional content management systems will never be the same and Drupal has shown how success is defined in this space by having a common sense open architecture, a rich plug-in ecosystem, and embodiment of best practices for social CMS. I’m also bullish on enterprise versions of Drupal, like Acquia. yet there remains a nagging feeling that social software suites (see below) may ultimately become the center of focus for social in the workplace. Social CMS is the last mainstream model fo social media but there is long-term potential for trouble as consumer social networks and enterprise social software suites begin to encroach on the feature space ... "
(http://www.dachisgroup.com/2010/08/the-2010-social-business-landscape/)


